Same comment: it has been like this before, the only change in this PR is to put common code inside the common CacheItem instead of implementing twice in MessageCacheItem and FormatCacheItem. Let's make any code logic change separately.
Also, only the setters inside child classes (MessageCacheItem, PatternCacheItem, LocaleCAcheItem) use this protected setTimestamp.The setters are synchronized and have the following signature:
public synchronized void setCacheItem(String etag, long timestamp, Long maxAgeMillis)

